<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#000050"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Naroon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Hey guys...  With all these various calculations about damage per second and such.  I have another question about something that, in my opinion, is rather hard to quantify.  I do not know if Romidar Trueblade took this into consideration with all this <B>wonderful</B>  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/cool.gif"> information.  But what about riposte?<P>I mean, honestly, it is a free attack on a mob.  And if I have to riposte  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/wink.gif">, I would rather have a free attack with my 25/50 Exec Axe compared to my 8/24 Yakk.  I simply hit harder with my axe.<P>Anyone put any thought into this?  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/confused.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Blackacid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Riposte is great, no doubts there - but it wont change your damage output by any large margin - so, it's generally not added into the mix.<P>I agree though, I'd rather riposte for 80dmg, instead fo 30.  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P><P>------------------<BR><B>Tezrian Vrix of Quellious</B><P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Beldukil</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Statistically riposts are rare enough that they dont add much damage. <P>Beld</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">PackMan97</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Also what happens when you are swinging three times as much with those Yaks? Three times as many chances to get Riposte'd yourself...when critters are hitting for 80pts a pop...that's gotta hurt!<P>[note] this thought was not my own..I shamelessly ripped it off someone else and am attempting to take credit for it =) *grins and Cauld*<P>------------------<BR>-Alewuf Shinkicker of Povar<BR>Gem Chopper of the 37thRank<P>"Put on your shinkickers and kick some shin!" -me<p>[This message has been edited by PackMan97 (edited February 11, 2000).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Cauldyth</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica"><BR>Yeah, Wuf brings up a point.  When fighting tougher mobs, especially Planar ones, they can Riposte like crazy, and those Ripostes can do 100-200 points of damage EACH.  Heck, after this topic was brought up on my guild's message boards yesterday, I decided to pay attention during fights last night.  A green gargoyle in Mistmoore riposted against me three times in one fight.  When you fight higher level critters, they get even better at it (and hit harder with each Riposte).<P><BR>Cauldyth Arranen<BR>Wood Elf Warrior<BR>Povar<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">treestout</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I think 2 handers like the mith are more suited for a defensive stance, while dual wielding is more suited for offense.  This all due to the aforementioned riposte ability.  Keeping the mob on you should be of prime importance.  If this is being accomplished, then i'd use a 2 hander for high blues-red mobs and dual ssoys for low blues.  Too bad many high red creatures require dual wield to keep on you reliably.<P><P>------------------<BR>"First you cleave the knee, then you cleave the head."<P>Meyer Anklebane,<BR>on taking down Hill Giants<BR>45 Halfling Warrior, Xegony<P>"I am NOT a smurf!  There are no smurfs in Everquest!"</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kailyn of Povar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I think that riposted treats all weapons as if they are ready to fire, so that theoretically you could get a quad hit repost....I will watch my logs.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Raggrok Skullcrusha</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Um, Kailyn- hate to say it but you are smoking crack. =)<P>Riposte always has been a single strike back.<P>------------------<BR>-Raggrok Skullcrusha<P>50th Ogre Warrior; RZ</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Kailyn of Povar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">You sure?<P>I was fairly sure you could atleast get primary and double, if not both hands, doubled.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Wisted</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Must be really bad crack.<BR>Riposte = Single Hit.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">TheAtomicKid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">I personally have never gotten more than a single hit from a single riposted attack.<P>However. There does seem to be a delay factor on it... in that, once I acquired my mith 2h, I started defending (dodge/parry/riposte) quite a bit more frequently than before. I would assume that any haste item would have this affect. (just an observation)<P><P>------------------<BR>Haast.<P>I am the thunder. I am the lighting. I am the raging heart of the storm, and the rock on which the ocean breaks, and retreats. I am War.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Rani</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">From parsing my logs i know that my riposte rate is about 4-5%(at lvl 50 with maxed skills). Worth keeping in mind when choosing weapons, but its not enough to get me to dump my dual ykeshas in favor of say a mith2h.<P>Rani</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Taermon</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Whose got crack?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Immudan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Well I have riposted two attacks in a row before so maybe that's what Kailyn was thinking of.  I'm pretty sure I've never gotten more than one attack from a riposte, but you'd have to look at log timestamps to be sure.<P>I'd never thought much about the fact that swinging more often would result in more mob ripostes, but now that I think about it I could see it being significant.  Has anyone ever looked at how much damage mobs rack up from ripostes?  I'm too lazy to do log analysis myself  <IMG SRC="http://boards.stratics.com/forums/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Khumak - 46 Ogre Warrior<BR>Hasima - 8 Dark Elf Necro<BR>Immudan - 11 Erudite Wizard<BR>(Rodcet Nife)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">Bushka</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Tahoma, Arial, Helvetica">not 100% on this cos i never thought bout it before but i dont think that person be on crack...yer riposte yer get one hit but that hit CAN be a double attack hence if yer riposte with yer executioner axe which is a lil slower then a ssoy you see it more clearly you can go chop chop instead of just ermmm chop? get what der ogre is sayin?<P>BUSHKA<BR>45th SUMMER OF DISCO<